BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Tr. Mercury conjunction Mars
DESCRIPTION:Transit Mercury (Gemini 24°26’) - conjunction - Natal Mars \nYou will feel very strong and energetic mentally. However, you will also be impatient with people who are unable to keep up with you and your thoughts. So, try to be more patient. You will be very productive, and you will be able to quickly evaluate all situations and turn your plans into action. Be careful when driving and handling sharp objects, you may injure yourself; you may also get into trouble while driving.  \n \nTransit Mercury in Natal 9th house: \nNow is one of the best times for studying and career development. If you want to enrol in a university or start looking for a new job, do it now!  \nNow you are a great storyteller and other people will love listening to your stories. You can fully use your creativity when writing, learning and communicating with people, especially those from university environment and from other cultures. Now you can also learn new languages with ease. Overall, you will be tolerant of alternative views, ideas and thoughts. It is also possible that you will get a great new idea that will bring you success.  \n \nPersonal Transit Calendar:  \nhttps://horoscopes.astro-seek.com/personal-transit-calendar-monthly-astrology-transits
DTSTART:20260529T082500Z
DTEND:20260529T082500Z
DTSTAMP:20260403T165714Z
UID:35_tr_me_co_ma
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Tr. Mercury trine Uranus
DESCRIPTION:Transit Mercury (Gemini 25°58’) - trine - Natal Uranus \nDuring this transit you will search for mental stimuli and exciting experiences that disrupt your daily routine. You may take part in non-traditional meetings where you can meet new people or find controversial information. You will visit one place after another, and your days will be full of activities. This is good because during this transit you will not be happy if you have to stay in one place for a long time.  \n \nTransit Mercury in Natal 9th house: \nNow is one of the best times for studying and career development. If you want to enrol in a university or start looking for a new job, do it now!  \nNow you are a great storyteller and other people will love listening to your stories. You can fully use your creativity when writing, learning and communicating with people, especially those from university environment and from other cultures. Now you can also learn new languages with ease. Overall, you will be tolerant of alternative views, ideas and thoughts. It is also possible that you will get a great new idea that will bring you success.  \n \nPersonal Transit Calendar:  \nhttps://horoscopes.astro-seek.com/personal-transit-calendar-monthly-astrology-transits
DTSTART:20260530T044100Z
DTEND:20260530T044100Z
DTSTAMP:20260403T165714Z
UID:36_tr_me_tr_ur
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Tr. Sun opposition Neptune
DESCRIPTION:Transit Sun (Gemini 9°22’) - opposition - Natal Neptune \nYou lack energy and feel exhausted. You may also be unable to concentrate. It is a good idea to focus on creative things. However, beware of excessive fantasies.  \n \nTransit Sun in Natal 9th house: \nIt’s time to expand your horizons! This transit usually brings new discoveries.  \nYou may have the urge to seek the meaning of life and you will be open to alternative views. It is a good time to travel longer distances and get to know different cultures. If you are not traveling anywhere, you can expect more interactions with people from other countries or different backgrounds. There may be problems with your father.  \nIt is also an ideal time for education, especially in the field of philosophy, where you will be more interested in various religious movements. If you already belong to a religion, more intensive engagement is expected - for example, you can go to church more often, engage in church activities, etc. During this period, you will also listen more to your guts and intuition. At the same time, you will not be afraid to discuss these topics with others because this transit supports sincerity. But be careful not to be rude and intolerant.  \n \n \nPersonal Transit Calendar:  \nhttps://horoscopes.astro-seek.com/personal-transit-calendar-monthly-astrology-transits
DTSTART:20260530T185900Z
DTEND:20260530T185900Z
DTSTAMP:20260403T165714Z
UID:37_tr_su_op_ne
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Tr. Sun opposition Moon
DESCRIPTION:Transit Sun (Gemini 10°13’) - opposition - Natal Moon \nBe careful not to act impulsively and do things without thinking carefully first. It is not a good time to start something new and you may feel frustrated when you do not see the results of your work. There may also be quarrels in your romantic relationship. You may not feel very well physically, you may be exhausted, feel weak or even get sick. Keep your head cool and wait until this stressful period passes knowing that you will feel better in a while.  \n \nTransit Sun in Natal 9th house: \nIt’s time to expand your horizons! This transit usually brings new discoveries.  \nYou may have the urge to seek the meaning of life and you will be open to alternative views. It is a good time to travel longer distances and get to know different cultures. If you are not traveling anywhere, you can expect more interactions with people from other countries or different backgrounds. There may be problems with your father.  \nIt is also an ideal time for education, especially in the field of philosophy, where you will be more interested in various religious movements. If you already belong to a religion, more intensive engagement is expected - for example, you can go to church more often, engage in church activities, etc. During this period, you will also listen more to your guts and intuition. At the same time, you will not be afraid to discuss these topics with others because this transit supports sincerity. But be careful not to be rude and intolerant.  \n \n \nPersonal Transit Calendar:  \nhttps://horoscopes.astro-seek.com/personal-transit-calendar-monthly-astrology-transits
DTSTART:20260531T161700Z
DTEND:20260531T161700Z
DTSTAMP:20260403T165714Z
